<span class="date">September 19, 2013</span>
<span class="pingcontent"><p>[&#8230;] The Law Revisions Are Not the Cause of Child Abandonment [&#8230;]</p>
</span>
</li> 
<li id="comment-668">
<span class="author"><a href='http://www.creatingafamily.org/blog/controversial-baby-boxes-for-abandoned-babies-in-china-korea/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Controversial Baby Boxes for Abandoned Babies In China-Korea</a></span> -
<span class="date">December 3, 2013</span>
<span class="pingcontent"><p>[&#8230;] Proponents of the new adoption law acknowledge that more infants are being abandoned, but say that it is due to other factors and a misunderstanding by pregnant single women of the requirements of the new law. It should be noted that the new adoption law has not been in effect for very long and understanding of the requirements are not widely known. [&#8230;]</p>
</span>
</li> 
</ol>
